Furthermore, the original testing chamber later became more and more dangerous as the full ramifications of  slowly lost strength, became more and more brittle, and eventually crumbled. The inverse effect was seen in surfaces which were closed. Some samples still remain, but their study showed no definitive reason for the cause of the effect.

